00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:11,080
Look.
看。

198
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:15,480
In a digital world, even the strongest must fight for survival.
在数字世界里，即使是最强者也必须为生存而战。

199
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:26,680
Two people possess a secret so valuable, so powerful,
两个人拥有一个如此珍贵、如此强大的秘密，

200
00:10:26,680 --> 00:10:30,320
they have to defend it at all costs.
他们必须不惜一切代价保护它。

201
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:31,760
I don't care where they are.
我不在乎他们在哪里。

202
00:10:31,760 --> 00:10:33,680
I don't care what it takes.
我不在乎要付出什么代价。

203
00:10:33,680 --> 00:10:37,600
You find them and bring them to me.
你找到他们，把他们带到我面前。

204
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:42,600
They only had one chance and their chance was to fight back.
他们只有一次机会，那就是反击。

205
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:48,600
You want to play rough?
你想来硬的？

206
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:50,600
Say hello to my little friend.
跟我的小朋友打个招呼吧。

207
00:10:56,600 --> 00:11:00,600
With a little help from the governor.
在州长的帮助下。

208
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:01,600
Listen to me.
听我说。

209
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:03,080
We have to get them out of there.
我们必须把他们弄出来。

210
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:05,080
No matter what.
无论如何。

211
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:08,600
Nothing will prevent them from doing their job.
没有什么能阻止他们完成工作。

212
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,600
Double the action.
双倍的动作。

213
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:12,080
Get down.
趴下。

214
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:14,080
Triple the excitement.
三倍的刺激。

215
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:16,080
Get down again.
再趴下。

216
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:20,080
This summer, nothing will stand in their way.
这个夏天，没有什么能阻挡他们。

217
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:25,080
I'm going to make them an offer again, people.
我要再给他们一个提议，各位。

218
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:27,080
Two hosts.
两位主持人。

219
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:29,080
One podcast.
一个播客。

220
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:31,080
EnglishPod.
EnglishPod。

221
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:33,080
Coming to a theatre near you.
即将来到你附近的影院。

222
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:40,080
I know that you're a big movie fan, right?
我知道你是个大影迷，对吧？

223
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:42,080
Yeah, I'm a big movie fan.
是的，我是个超级影迷。

224
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:44,080
I usually watch maybe three or five movies a week.
我通常每周看三到五部电影。

225
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:45,080
Really?
真的吗？

226
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,080
Yeah, yeah.
是啊，是啊。

227
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:47,080
Wow.
哇。

228
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:48,080
How do you like the movie?
你觉得这部电影怎么样？

229
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:49,080
I love the movie.
我很喜欢这部电影。

230
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:50,080
You like the movie?
你喜欢这部电影吗？

231
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:51,080
I love the movie.
我很喜欢这部电影。

232
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:52,080
I love the movie.
我很喜欢这部电影。

233
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:53,080
I love the movie.
我很喜欢这部电影。

234
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:55,080
Really?
真的吗？

235
00:11:55,080 --> 00:12:00,080
Many students of English like to watch movies as a way to improve their English.
很多英语学习者喜欢通过看电影来提高英语水平。

236
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:05,080
That's one of the best ways to learn English is through songs and movies.
通过歌曲和电影学习英语是最好的方法之一。

237
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:09,080
What do you think are some useful movies that people can watch to practice English?
你觉得有哪些有用的电影可以让人用来练习英语？

238
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:11,080
Well, I would recommend children's movies.
嗯，我会推荐儿童电影。

239
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:12,080
Really?
真的吗？

240
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:16,080
Yeah, they have simple vocabulary, but they have very common language.
是的，它们的词汇简单，但语言很常用。

241
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:20,080
And also, what's happening in the movie is very easy to understand and to follow.
而且，电影里发生的事情很容易理解和跟上。

242
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:23,080
So you can see the action and then hear the word.
所以你可以看到动作，然后听到单词。

243
00:12:23,080 --> 00:12:24,080
Exactly.
没错。

244
00:12:24,080 --> 00:12:33,080
So if you like to watch movies, rent a DVD or go buy a DVD, watch it in the original language with English subtitles.
所以如果你喜欢看电影，租一张DVD或者去买一张DVD，用原声加英文字幕看。

245
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:35,080
So you should watch it in English.
所以你应该看英文版的。

246
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:37,080
With English subtitles.
带英文字幕。

247
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:39,080
Yeah, and what are subtitles?
嗯，什么是字幕？

248
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:44,080
Subtitles are the words that you see at the bottom of the screen that translate what the people are saying.
字幕就是你在屏幕底部看到的文字，用来翻译人们说的话。

249
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:45,080
Okay.
好的。

250
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:46,080
Yeah, that's the best thing to do.
是的，这是最好的做法。

